# Request Properties

The `req` object (http.IncomingMessage) contains information about the request.

Important properties:
- `req.method`: HTTP method (GET, POST, etc.)
- `req.url`: the URL path (e.g., '/about')
- `req.headers`: object with request headers
- `req.socket`: underlying socket (rarely used)

```javascript
const server = http.createServer((req, res) => {
  console.log(`${req.method} ${req.url}`);
});
```

slides.codeSnippet:
const http = require('http');

const server = http.createServer((req, res) => {
  res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'text/plain' });
  res.end(`You requested: ${req.method} ${req.url}`);
});

server.listen(3000);
